Wolframe is a modular 3-tier application server framework.

It runs natively on Windows, Linux, Mac OSX, BSDs and Solaris.

Its modular structure allows the system to be extended with new languages
for the business logic layer (Python, Lua), new SQL database drivers (SQLite3,
PostgreSQL, Oracle), document formats (XML, JSON), printing, etc.

The project started as idea in 2008, the GitGub repository was created on
Feb 11, 2010. 
